  What We Chose Not to Build

  Equally important: we recognized when a pattern doesn't fit.

  The discriminated union exploration (Option D) demonstrated that the current ParsedActivityLine design is already optimal - all fields are shared, multi-context  activities are valid.

  Adding 14 nearly-identical dataclasses would have added complexity without proportional benefit.

  This is the "deal with fundamentals" philosophy in action - not every type safety pattern is appropriate for every situation.

